laboratory_examinations.findings: Negative on skin prick tests with a large panel of commercial food extracts (Abello 1 : 20 w/v).
Did not elicit any wheal and flare reaction.
Sodium benzoate 100 mg caused a relapse of diffuse pruritus that lasted for 48 hours.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: This finding was confirmed by a second series of double blind, placebo-controlled challenges, where sodium benzoate again induced pruritus that appeared about 24 hours after the administration and lasted for 5 days.
